# 🍲 Recipe Sharing API

## 📌 Description

Recipe Sharing API ek RESTful backend application hai jisme users recipes create, read, update aur delete kar sakte hain. Isme JWT-based authentication, role-based access control, aur multiuser support implement kiya gaya hai.

---

## 🚀 Features

* 🔐 JWT Authentication (Login/Register)
* 👥 Role-Based Access Control (Admin & User)
* 🍲 CRUD Operations for Recipes
* 💬 Comment System
* 👤 Multiuser Support (User-specific recipes)
* 🔗 Populate (User details with recipes)
* 📡 RESTful API Structure

---

## 🛠️ Tech Stack

* Node.js
* Express.js
* MongoDB
* Mongoose
* JSON Web Token (JWT)
* bcryptjs

## 🔑 API Endpoints

### 🔐 Authentication

* `POST /api/auth/register` → Register user
* `POST /api/auth/login` → Login user

---

### 🍲 Recipes

* `GET /api/recipes` → Get all recipes
* `POST /api/recipes` → Create recipe (Auth required)
* `PUT /api/recipes/:id` → Update recipe (Owner/Admin)
* `DELETE /api/recipes/:id` → Delete recipe (Owner/Admin)
* `GET /api/recipes/my` → Get logged-in user recipes

---

### 💬 Comments

* `POST /api/comments` → Add comment
* `GET /api/comments/:recipeId` → Get comments for a recipe

---

## 🔐 Authentication Method

* JWT token use hota hai authentication ke liye
* Token login ke baad response me milta hai

### 📌 Example:

```
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_TOKEN_HERE
```

---

## ⚙️ Installation & Setup

1. Clone the repository:

```
git clone <your-repo-link>
```

2. Install dependencies:

```
npm install
```

3. Create `.env` file:

```
PORT=5000
MONGO_URI=your_mongodb_connection
JWT_SECRET=your_secret_key
```

4. Start the server:

```
npm start
```

---

## 📡 Testing API

* Postman
* Thunder Client (VS Code extension)

---

## 👤 User Roles

| Role  | Permissions                            |
| ----- | -------------------------------------- |
| Admin | Full access (delete/update any recipe) |
| User  | Can manage own recipes only            |

---

## 🔗 Populate Example

Recipes me user details show karne ke liye:

```js
Recipe.find().populate('createdBy', 'username email')
```